Reasoning: The paper deals with the uplink performance of massive MIMO systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of multiple antennas by users and the consideration of spatially correlated multipath fading suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of the Weichselberger correlation model and the focus on spectral efficiency make the paper relevant to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the consideration of future system designs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computer communications (cs.COM).
